@schema_version 1
@project n00b-audit-test
@description Fixture with a required per-rule field absent -- loader must SCHEMA-reject. Pre-WP-009-Phase-2 this fixture omitted the bnf_fragment block (which used to be required); WP-009 Phase 2 made bnf_fragment OPTIONAL (query-mode rules ship without one), so the fixture now omits a different required field (@guidance) instead. The rule body below also has no <...> productions so it doubles as evidence the loader is happy with an empty bnf_body when the only remaining problem is the missing @guidance directive.
@source_doc test/fixtures/naudit/guidance_missing_field.bnf
@dependencies

@rule n00b.s2_1.null
@title NULL -> nullptr
@section section 2.1
@violation_nt placeholder_in_phase_3
@rationale C23 has nullptr; NULL is a legacy macro.
@bad int *p = NULL;
@good int *p = nullptr;
